				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Since the format isn't equipped with a designated cancel button, i think most titles try to stay away from menu diving. I have a hard time recalling a comprehensive collection of examples, but <em>Castlevania III - Dracula's Curse</em> has one such:<br /><br />Sel+a+b and start brings the secret music menu. From there, B starts music, A stops. Start returns/exits. Select does nothing. Speaking of which, i remember always pressing on A first which does nothing since no music has started playing yet  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" />  <br /><br />One could argue SMB1 and many other games takes you back from demo to title screen by pressing start. I'd say it is the 'yes, go on' button.</div>

					
